  "text": "The volume of gastric and duodenal samples was determined to the closest millilitre and corrected for loss by reference to PEG recovery (see under Calculations and statistics below). The pH was monitored repeatedly during the test and in each [CITATION_1] ml portion. It did not decrease below 6. Trypsin activity was determined using TAME (p-toluolsulphonyl-l-arginin-methylester) as substrate by the method of Hummel. '7 Amylase and lipase activities and bilirubin and bile acid content were determined by the use of commercially available kits. PEG was measured by turbidimetry using the method of ",
